C=====True=====72
Stanley Forman won a Pulitzer for a picture in this city that shows Joseph Rakes attacking Ted
Landsmark with an American flag. Morgan v. Hennigan ruled that this city’s busing policy had created
de facto segregation. In 1998, a federal court ruled that this city’s Latin school, the oldest public school
in the United States, could no longer consider race when accepting students. For the point, name this city
that, in 2018, stopped honoring racist owner Tom Yawkey with a street name outside Fenway Park, where
the Red Sox play in Massachusetts.=====
Boston
=====